{"title_page": "Jerry Slijngard", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name          = Jerry Slijngard\n| image         = Jerry Slijngard (cropped).jpg\n| alt           = Jerry Slijngard\n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date    = \n| birth_place   = \n| death_date    = \n| death_place   = \n| nationality   = [[Suriname]]\n| other_names   = \n| occupation    = Director Coast Guard <br> Director National Coordination Centre for Emergency Management (NCCR)\n| years_active  = \n| known_for     = \n| notable_works = \n}}\n\n'''Jerry Slingard''' is a [[Surinamese people|Surinamese]] soldier and official. Jerry Slingard has the rank of [[ colonel]]. In 2003 he was appointed to head the National Coordination Centre for Emergency Management (NCCR). <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://parbode.com/klaar-voor-de-ramp/|title=Ready for the disaster (in Dutch)|access-date=6 April 2020|website=Parbode}}</ref>\nIn 2013 he was appointed to head the newly created [[Coast Guard]]. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.starnieuws.com/index.php/welcome/index/nieuwsitem/17870|title=Slijngaard: Boat first visible result Coast Guard (in Dutch)|access-date=6 April 2020|website=Star Nieuws}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://gov.sr/themas/veiligheid-en-orde/kustwacht/|title=Coast Guard (in Dutch)|website=gov.sr|access-date=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Corona epidemic==\nAt the announcement of the first Covid-19 infection in Suriname, Slijngard was appointed  as a member of the National COVID-19 Managementteam. After [[Antoine Joly]], the [[France|French]] ambassador to Suriname, tested positive on 24 April 2020, <ref name=\"antoine_joly\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.dwtonline.com/laatste-nieuws/2020/03/25/franse-ambassadeur-in-isolatie-in-wanica-ziekenhuis/|title=French Ambassador in isolation in Wanica Hospital (in Dutch)|access-date=4 April 2020|website=De Ware Tijd}}</ref> [[Danielle Veira]], the Director of the COVID-19 Managementteam, went into quarantine, and <ref name=\"quarantine\">{{Cite news|url=https://fathh.com/suriname/nieuws/118007/franse-ambassadeur-8ste-covid-19-slachtoffer.html|title=France Ambassador 8th Covid 19 victim (in Dutch)|website=Suriname News|access-date=6 April 2020}}</ref> Jerry Slijgard was temporarily appointed as her successor. <ref name=\"quarantine\"/> Veira  returned to resume her duties on 2 April 2020. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.srherald.com/suriname/2020/04/02/dnv-directeur-veira-uit-quarantaine/|title=Director DNV Veira out of quarantine|access-date=6 April 2020|website=Suriname Herald}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Slijngard, Jerry}}\n{{Suriname-bio-stub}}\n[[Category:Surinamese military personnel]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name          = Jerry Slijngard\n| image         = Jerry Slijngard (cropped).jpg\n| alt           = Jerry Slijngard\n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date    = \n| birth_place   = \n| death_date    = \n| death_place   = \n| nationality   = [[Suriname]]\n| other_names   = \n| occupation    = Director Coast Guard <br> Director National Coordination Centre for Emergency Management (NCCR)\n| years_active  = \n| known_for     = \n| notable_works = \n}}\n\n'''Jerry Slingard''' is a [[Surinamese people|Surinamese]] soldier and official. Jerry Slingard has the rank of [[ colonel]]. In 2003 he was appointed to head the National Coordination Centre for Emergency Management (NCCR). <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://parbode.com/klaar-voor-de-ramp/|title=Ready for the disaster (in Dutch)|access-date=6 April 2020|website=Parbode}}</ref>\nIn 2013 he was appointed to head the newly created [[Coast Guard]]. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.starnieuws.com/index.php/welcome/index/nieuwsitem/17870|title=Slijngaard: Boat first visible result Coast Guard (in Dutch)|access-date=6 April 2020|website=Star Nieuws}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://gov.sr/themas/veiligheid-en-orde/kustwacht/|title=Coast Guard (in Dutch)|website=gov.sr|access-date=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Corona epidemic==\nAt the announcement of the first Covid-19 infection in Suriname, Slijngard was appointed  as a member of the National COVID-19 Managementteam. After [[Antoine Joly]], the [[France|French]] ambassador to Suriname, tested positive on 24 April 2020, <ref name=\"antoine_joly\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.dwtonline.com/laatste-nieuws/2020/03/25/franse-ambassadeur-in-isolatie-in-wanica-ziekenhuis/|title=French Ambassador in isolation in Wanica Hospital (in Dutch)|access-date=4 April 2020|website=De Ware Tijd}}</ref> [[Danielle Veira]] went into quarantine, and <ref name=\"quarantine\">{{Cite news|url=https://fathh.com/suriname/nieuws/118007/franse-ambassadeur-8ste-covid-19-slachtoffer.html|title=France Ambassador 8th Covid 19 victim (in Dutch)|website=Suriname News|access-date=6 April 2020}}</ref> Jerry Slijgard was temporarily appointed as her successor. <ref name=\"quarantine\"/> Veira  returned to resume her duties on 2 April 2020. <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.srherald.com/suriname/2020/04/02/dnv-directeur-veira-uit-quarantaine/|title=Director DNV Veira out of quarantine|access-date=6 April 2020|website=Suriname Herald}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Slijngard, Jerry}}\n{{Suriname-bio-stub}}\n[[Category:Surinamese military personnel]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "name_user": "KittenKlub", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jerry_Slijngard"}
{"title_page": "Smallfoot (film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2018 film directed by Karey Kirkpatrick}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Smallfoot\n| image          = Smallfoot (film).png\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Karey Kirkpatrick]]\n| producer       = {{unbulleted list|Bonne Radford|[[Glenn Ficarra]]|[[John Requa]]}}\n| screenplay     = {{unbulleted list|Karey Kirkpatrick|Clare Sera}}\n| story          = {{unbulleted list|John Requa|Glenn Ficarra|Karey Kirkpatrick}}\n| based on       = {{based on|''Yeti Tracks'' (unpublished)|[[Sergio Pablos]]}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|<!--Per poster billing-->\n* [[Channing Tatum]]\n* [[James Corden]]\n* [[Zendaya]]\n* [[Common (rapper)|Common]]\n* [[LeBron James]]\n* [[Danny DeVito]]\n* [[Gina Rodriguez]]\n* [[Yara Shahidi]]\n* [[Ely Henry]]\n* [[Jimmy Tatro]]\n}}\n| music          = [[Heitor Pereira]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://filmmusicreporter.com/2017/11/21/heitor-pereira-to-score-smallfoot/|title=Heitor Pereira to Score 'Smallfoot'|website=Film Music Reporter|date=November 21, 2018|accessdate=November 25, 2018}}</ref>\n| cinematography          = Stephen W. Childers \n| editing        = Peter Ettinger\n| production companies = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Warner Animation Group]]\n* Zaftig Films<ref name=\"varietyinsight\">{{cite web |title=Film releases |url=https://www.varietyinsight.com/print_featurefilm_releases.php?sort=&from_date= |website=[[Variety Insight]] |publisher=[[Variety Media]] |accessdate=August 7, 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n| distributor    = [[Warner Bros.|Warner Bros. Pictures]]<ref name=\"varietyinsight\" />\n| released       = {{Film date|2018|9|28|United States}}\n| runtime        = 96 minutes<ref>{{cite web |title=Smallfoot (3D)|url=https://www.bbfc.co.uk/releases/smallfoot-film |website=[[British Board of Film Classification]]|date=September 14, 2018|accessdate=September 25, 2018}}</ref>\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         = $80 million<ref name=BOpreview/>\n| gross          = $214 million<ref name=\"BOM\">{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=smallfoot.htm|title=Smallfoot (2018)|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=January 7, 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Smallfoot''''' is a 2018 American  [[computer-animated]] [[Musical film|musical]] [[comedy film]] produced by the [[Warner Animation Group]] and distributed by [[Warner Bros.|Warner Bros. Pictures]]. Based on the unpublished children's book ''Yeti Tracks'' by [[Sergio Pablos]], the film was co-written and directed by [[Karey Kirkpatrick]], and stars the voices of [[Channing Tatum]], [[James Corden]], [[Zendaya]], [[Common (rapper)|Common]], [[LeBron James]], [[Gina Rodriguez]], [[Danny DeVito]], [[Yara Shahidi]], [[Ely Henry]], and [[Jimmy Tatro]]. The plot follows a group of [[Yeti]] who come across a human, with each species thinking the other was just a myth.\n\n''Smallfoot'' was theatrically released in the United States on September 28, 2018. It received a moderately positive reception from critics and was a box office success, grossing over $214 million worldwide.\n\n== Plot ==\n<!-- Per WP:FILMPLOT, plot summaries for featured film articles should be 400 to 700 words. -->\nA village of [[Yeti]]s lives in isolation on the top of a mountain in the [[Himalayas]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Mitchell|first=Peter|url=https://www.news.com.au/world/breaking-news/channing-tatum-belts-out-tune-in-smallfoot/news-story/8aad30b072ffad2b0e520d16a2fee43d|title=Channing Tatum belts out tune in Smallfoot|website=News.co.au|archivedate=September 20, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> above the clouds and hidden away from sight. Migo is a yeti who abides by the law of the ancient stones held by the Stonekeeper, the yetis' leader. Migo's father, Dorgle, projects himself through the air each morning to hit a gong with his head, as the yetis believe this allows the sun to rise. While learning how to ring the gong, Migo is distracted by the Stonekeeper's daughter, Meechee, whom he has a crush on, and misses the gong, landing outside the village. There, Migo witnesses a plane crash and finds a \"smallfoot\" (human), whom the yetis believe is mythical. Migo runs back to inform the villagers, but because he lacks proof, Stonekeeper claims he is lying and banishes him from the village. Migo is suddenly visited by rejected yetis Gwangi, Kolka, and Fleem who bring him to the Smallfoot Evidentiary Society, which is led by Meechee. She convinces Migo travel below the clouds despite the stones telling them that there is nothing underneath. After some hesitation, Migo agrees to go, but his rope snaps and Migo falls, where he discovers land.\n\nPercy Patterson is a British human filmmaker of wildlife documentaries who has lost most of his viewership. He meets the pilot who saw Migo, and in an attempt to regain his fame, tries unsuccessfully to convince his assistant, Brenda, to dress up as a yeti for filming. Migo arrives and unknowingly scares Percy when trying to communicate with him. Migo takes Percy with him and they stop in a cave to wait out a blizzard. Percy films and uploads a video of Migo narrating that the Yeti plans to eat him, before attempting to escape. While chasing Percy, Migo's toe becomes caught in a bear trap and Percy takes pity on him by removing the trap and bandaging Migo's wound. Percy agrees to go with Migo and they head back up the mountain, where they reunite with the S.E.S.\n\nThe villagers are confused by Percy's appearance, but happily accept him and learn about his culture, much to Stonekeeper's dismay. Afterwards, Stonekeeper takes Migo inside the palace and reveals the truth: yetis used to live below the clouds, but were forced into hiding by the humans who attacked them. To keep them safe, they created the stones, and the clouds are actually steam made by the yetis' daily tasks to keep them hidden. In order to protect the village, Migo agrees to continue the lie by telling the yetis that Percy, who is experiencing [[high altitude sickness]], is just a hairless [[wild yak]]. Stonekeeper takes Percy and locks him in a box, so Percy will be unable to alert other humans of the yetis' whereabouts. Migo later discovers that Meechee took Percy away to return him home, and jumps down the mountain with Gwangi and Kolka following suit.\n\nPercy recovers and discovers that his video of Migo has generated public excitement, but then notices that Meechee has become distracted by the wonders in [[Kathmandu]] and accidentally causes a disruption. Meechee is attacked by the police, but is rescued by Gwangi, Kolka and Migo. The yetis try to make it back to the mountain, but are chased by a SWAT helicopter that Stonekeeper takes down using his stones. Migo attempts to divert the police away from the other yetis, when Percy arrives on his snowmobile and shoots Migo with a tranquilizer gun to save him. The police chase and capture Percy in his yeti suit, and arrest him for public disturbance and fraud.\n\nBack at the village, inside the palace, Migo and Stonekeeper explain the truth to the yetis while Migo apologizes for lying to them. Migo tells the others that even though humans may still be scared of the yetis, they should try to communicate with them. The yetis leave the village, and when Percy and Brenda notice them, they emerge from the crowd and stand up for the yetis. The rest of the humans slowly welcome the yetis and accept them into their lives.\n\n== Voice cast ==\n*[[Channing Tatum]] as Migo, a young male [[yeti]] who is determined to prove the existence of the Smallfoot.\n*[[James Corden]] as Percy Patterson, a British [[human]] [[filmmaker]] of wildlife documentaries trying to get back in the spotlight, who becomes Migo's Smallfoot-best friend.\n*[[Zendaya]] as Meechee, a young female yeti, the Stonekeeper's daughter, Thorp's younger sister, the leader of S.E.S., and Migo's love interest.\n*[[Common (rapper)|Common]] as Stonekeeper, the condescending yeti [[Tribal chief|chief]] and father of Thorp and Meechee.\n*[[LeBron James]] as Gwangi, a large purple male yeti who is part of the S.E.S.\n*[[Gina Rodriguez]] as Kolka, a female yeti who is part of the S.E.S.\n*[[Danny DeVito]] as Dorgle, a short male yeti who is the village gong ringer and Migo's widowed father.\n*[[Yara Shahidi]] as Brenda, Percy's co-worker for his show and his morally conscious assistant, who doesn't believe in yetis until the end of the movie.\n*[[Ely Henry]] as Fleem, a small male yeti who is part of the S.E.S.\n*[[Jimmy Tatro]] as Thorp, a slow-witted male yeti who's the Stonekeeper's son and Meechee's older brother.\n*[[Patricia Heaton]] as Mama Bear, a [[himalayan brown bear]] that Migo and Percy encounter in a cave while waiting out a blizzard.  In the UK release, the part of Mama Bear was performed by [[Emma Bunton]]. \n*[[Justin Roiland]] as Garry, a paranoid male yeti.\n*[[Jack Quaid]] as Pilot, a human airplane pilot who crashes on the mountain and who Migo first meets.\n\n== Production ==\n[[File:Yeti by Philippe Semeria.jpg|thumb|The legend of the [[Yeti]] and an original idea by [[Sergio Pablos]] inspired the story.]]\nWriters [[Glenn Ficarra]] and [[John Requa]] conceived of ''Smallfoot'', interested in a story about [[Yeti]] or [[Bigfoot]]; they drew inspiration from an original idea by [[Sergio Pablos]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metro.us/entertainment/movies/is-smallfoot-based-on-a-book |title=Is 'Smallfoot' based on a book? |website=[[Metro New York]] |last=Wakeman |first=Gregory |date=September 28, 2018 |accessdate=October 8, 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe concept for ''Smallfoot'' was in development before director [[Karey Kirkpatrick]] joined the project in July 2016; he viewed an [[animatic]] in which Percy was a \"ski bum type\". Kirkpatrick also said Meechee was undeveloped, and she was made head of the S.E.S. in rewrites.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/smallfoot-director-karey-kirkpatrick-interview/|title=Director Karey Kirkpatrick Reveals How Current Events Shaped 'Smallfoot' |work=[[Collider.com]] |last=Cook |first=Tommy |date=October 5, 2018 |accessdate=October 8, 2018}}</ref> Observing [[Brexit]] and a rise in nationalism, Kirkpatrick also drew inspiration:\n{{quote|Truth was under attack ... certainly phrases like [[alternative facts]] were being thrown around.  So, it became an age of misinformation fueled by agendas that are often fueled by fear. And like, 'I want this result, and so I am skewing the truth.' That is just in the zeitgeist.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://screenrant.com/smallfoot-director-interview-karey-kirkpatrick/ |title=Karey Kirkpatrick Interview: Smallfoot|work=[[Screen Rant]] |last=Deckelmeier |first=Joe |date=September 28, 2018 |accessdate=October 8, 2018}}</ref>}}\n\nOn May 11, 2017, it was announced that the film was in-production with [[Channing Tatum]], [[Zendaya]], and [[Gina Rodriguez]] providing the lead voice roles.<ref name=\"May2017THR\">{{cite news|last1=Kit|first1=Borys|title=Channing Tatum, Zendaya, Gina Rodriguez Lead Voice Cast for Yeti Tale 'Smallfoot'|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/channing-tatum-zendaya-gina-rodriguez-lead-voice-cast-yeti-tale-smallfoot-1002860|accessdate=May 12, 2017|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=May 11, 2017|language=en}}</ref> [[Ely Henry]] was originally hired as a [[scratch vocal]] for the film four years before its release, however was later invited to join the cast and subsequently voiced Fleem in the final product.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://terroirmag.com/articles/2018/9/29/self-care-in-the-creative-industries-with-ely-henry |title=Self Care in the Creative Industries with Ely Henry \u2014 Terroir Magazine |publisher=Terroirmag.com |date=2018-09-29 |accessdate=2019-09-30}}</ref> The film was animated by [[Sony Pictures Imageworks]], who had also provided animation for the [[Warner Animation Group]]'s ''[[Storks (film)|Storks]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.awn.com/animationworld/warner-and-imageworks-deliver-more-babies-storks|title=Warner and Imageworks Deliver More than Babies in 'Storks'|first=Dan|last=Sarto|website=[[Animation World Network]]|date=September 22, 2016|accessdate=November 24, 2018}}</ref> and utilized [[Autodesk Maya]] for the animation process.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://postperspective.com/creating-snow-hair-environments-warners-smallfoot/|title=Sony Imageworks provides big effects, animation for Warner's Smallfoot|date=October 3, 2018|first=Randi|last=Altman|website=postperspective.com|accessdate=November 24, 2018}}</ref> Ryan O'Loughlin, a [[DreamWorks Animation]] veteran, was originally the film's director, but was replaced by Kirkpatrick.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cartoonbrew.com/feature-film/warner-bros-unveils-smallfoot-teaser-trailer-154933.html|title=Warner Bros. Unveils 'Smallfoot' Teaser Trailer|work=Cartoon Brew|date=November 22, 2017|last1=Amidi|first1=Amid|accessdate=November 28, 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Music ===\nThe score for the film was composed by [[Heitor Pereira]]. The songs were written by Karey and [[Wayne Kirkpatrick]]. The film originally had no songs until six months into production when the suggestion of making the film a musical came from [[Toby Emmerich]], who was recently elected as chairman of the Warner Bros. Pictures Group at the time.<ref>{{cite web|last=McLean|first=Tom|url=http://www.animationmagazine.net/features/smallfoot-singing-with-sasquatch-friends/|title='Smallfoot': Singing with Sasquatch & Friends|website=Animation Magazine|date=September 3, 2018|accessdate=November 25, 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe songs include \"Perfection\" by Channing Tatum, \"Wonderful Life\" by Zendaya, \"Percy's Pressure\" by James Corden (music from the song \"[[Under Pressure]]\", additional lyrics by Karey and Wayne Kirkpatrick), \"Wonderful Questions\" by Tatum & Zendaya, \"Let It Lie\" by [[Common (rapper)|Common]], \"Moment of Truth\" by CYN, and \"Finally Free\" by [[Niall Horan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://watertower-music.com/releases/release.php?title=smallfoot|title=Smallfoot: Original Motion Picture Soundtrack|website=WaterTower Music|access-date=October 3, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\nThe film was released on September 28, 2018.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/festivals/annecy-warner-animation-group-smallfoot-1201795420/|title=Annecy: Warner Animation Group Sets 'Smallfoot' For a Spring 2018 Release|last=Hopewell|first=John|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=June 14, 2016|accessdate=May 12, 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Marketing ===\nThe first teaser trailer was released on November 22, 2017. The first official trailer was released on April 24, 2018. The final trailer was released on July 27, 2018. <ref>{{cite web |last1=Billington |first1=Alex |title=New Full-Length Trailer for Animated 'Smallfoot' Movie About Yetis |url=https://www.firstshowing.net/2018/official-full-length-trailer-for-animated-smallfoot-movie-about-yetis/|website=FirstShowing.net |date=April 25, 2018|accessdate=August 15, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn late summer 2018, American pizza chain [[Chuck E. Cheese's]] announced that they will be the official partner of the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ispot.tv/ad/dzFY/chuck-e-cheeses-all-you-can-play-smallfoot-collectible|title=Chuck E. Cheese's All You Can Play TV Commercial, 'Smallfoot Collectible'|website=iSpot.tv|language=en|accessdate=October 7, 2018}}</ref> Marketing materials for the film, in particular a series of posters in [[Los Angeles]] advertising the cast of the film with phrases such as \"[[Zendaya]] is Meechee\", turned into a minor [[Internet meme]] (in a short song by Gabriel Gundacker).<ref>{{cite news |last1=Bromwich |first1=Jonah |title=Zendaya Is Meechee Is a Post-Vine Vine |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/09/25/style/zendaya-is-meechee.html |accessdate=November 25, 2018 |work=The New York Times |date=September 25, 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Home media ===\n''Smallfoot'' was released on Digital on iTunes, Movies Anywhere, Microsoft Store, Vudu, and Amazon Prime on December 4, 2018, and on DVD, Blu-ray, Blu-Ray 3D,, and Digital Copy on December 11, 2018.<ref>https://www.mediaplaynews.com/smallfoot-to-march-to-digital-dec-4-disc-dec-11-from-warner/</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.target.com/p/smallfoot-blu-ray-dvd-digital/-/A-54150093|title=Smallfoot (Blu-Ray + DVD + Digital)|website=Target|accessdate=November 24, 2018}}</ref> The releases also included a short film, titled ''Super Soozie''.\n\n== Reception ==\n=== Box office ===\n''Smallfoot'' grossed $83.2 million in the United States and Canada, and $130.9 million in other territories, for a total worldwide gross of $214.1 million.<ref name=\"BOM\"/>\n\nIn the United States and Canada, ''Smallfoot'' was released alongside ''[[Night School (2018 film)|Night School]]'', ''[[Little Women (2018 film)|Little Women]]'' and ''[[Hell Fest]]'', and was projected to gross $25\u201330 million from 4,131 theaters in its opening weekend.<ref name=BOpreview>{{cite web |url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/la-fi-ct-movie-projector-small-foot-night-school-20180926-story.html|title=Kevin Hart and Tiffany Haddish's 'Night School' to battle 'Smallfoot' for box office crown|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|first=Ryan|last=Faughnder|date=September 26, 2018|accessdate=September 26, 2018}}</ref> The film made $6.5 million on its first day, including $850,000  from Thursday night previews, more than the Warner Animation Group's previous September release ''[[Storks (film)|Storks]]'' ($435,000 in 2016). It went on to debut to $23 million, finishing second at the box office behind ''Night School''.<ref name=opening>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/09/night-school-tiffany-haddish-kevin-hart-weekend-box-office-1202472883/|title='Night School' Top Of The Weekend's Box Office Class With $28M; Best Opening For A Comedy So Far This Year|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |publisher=[[Penske Business Media]] |date=September 30, 2018 |first=Anthony |last=D'Alessandro |accessdate=September 30, 2018}}</ref> It made $14.3 million in its second weekend and $9.1 million in its third, dropping 37% each time and finishing third and fifth, respectively.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/venom-a-star-is-born-weekend-box-office-lady-gaga-1202476614/|title='Venom' Flies To Near $90M; 'A Star Is Born' Has Rhythm With $51M As Monday Fall Holidays Propel Box Office|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|publisher=[[Penske Business Media]]|date=October 9, 2018 |first=Anthony |last= D'Alessandro|accessdate=October 9, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/first-man-landing-1m-from-thursday-night-shows-early-b-o-read-1202481481/|title='Sony Swings Past $1 Billion As 'Venom' Bites $35M+; 'First Man' Lands Third With $16M+ \u2013 Sunday AM|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|publisher=[[Penske Business Media]]|date=October 14, 2018 |first=Anthony |last= D'Alessandro|accessdate=October 14, 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Critical response ===\nOn [[review aggregator]] [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film holds an approval rating of 76% based on 122 reviews, with an [[Weighted arithmetic mean|average rating]] of 6.26/10. The website's critical consensus reads, \"''Smallfoot'' offers a colorful distraction that should keep younger viewers entertained - and a story whose message might even resonate with older audiences.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/smallfoot|title=Smallfoot (2018)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=February 7, 2020}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], the film has a weighted average score of 60 out of 100, based on 25 critics, indicating \"mixed or average reviews\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/smallfoot|title=Smallfoot reviews|website=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=October 15, 2018}}</ref> Audiences polled by [[CinemaScore]] gave the film an average grade of \"A\u2013\" on an A+ to F scale, while [[PostTrak]] reported filmgoers gave it 4 out of 5 stars.<ref name=opening/>\n\n=== Accolades ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Award/Event\n! Date of ceremony\n! Category\n! Recipient(s) and nominee(s)\n! Result\n! class=\"unsortable\"| {{Abbr|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Alliance of Women Film Journalists]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"|January 10, 2019\n| Best Animated Feature Film\n| [[Karey Kirkpatrick]]<br />Jason Reisig\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news |title=2018 EDA Award Nominees - Alliance of Women Film Journalists |url=https://awfj.org/eda-awards-2/2018-eda-award-nominees/ |accessdate=December 21, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best Animated Female\n| [[Zendaya]] <small>as Meechee</small>\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Annie Award]]s\n| February 2, 2019\n| [[Annie Award for Music in a Feature Production]] \n| Heitor Pereira, [[Karey Kirkpatrick]], [[Wayne Kirkpatrick]] \n| {{Nominated}} \n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|last=Flores|first=Terry|title=\u2018Incredibles 2,\u2019 \u2018Ralph Breaks the Internet\u2019 Top Annie Awards Nominations|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/incredibles-2-ralph-annie-awards-nominations-1203077216/|publisher=Variety|accessdate=December 7, 2018|date=December 3, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Detroit Film Critics Society]]\n| December 3, 2018\n| Best Animated Feature\n| rowspan=\"2\"|''Smallfoot''\n| {{nom}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news |title=The 2018 Detroit Film Critics Society Awards |url=https://detroitfilmcritics.com/the-2018-detroit-film-critics-society-awards/ |accessdate=December 21, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Heartland Film Festival]]\n| October 11\u201321, 2018\n| Truly Moving Picture Award\n| {{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news |title=Truly Moving Picture Award - Heartland Film |url=http://heartlandfilm.org/tmpa/ |accessdate=December 21, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Hollywood Music in Media Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[9th Hollywood Music in Media Awards|November 14, 2018]]\n| Original Score \u2013 Animated Film\n| [[Heitor Pereira]] \n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"HMMA18\">{{cite news |last1=Xu |first1=Linda |title=Hollywood Music in Media Awards: Full List of Winners |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/hollywood-music-media-awards-winners-2018-1153411 |accessdate=November 24, 2018 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=November 15, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| Original Song \u2013 Animated Film\n| [[Niall Horan]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|[[Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards|Kids' Choice Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"3\"|[[2019 Kids' Choice Awards|March 23, 2019]]\n| Favorite Male Voice from an Animated Movie\n| [[Channing Tatum]]\n| {{nom}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|Favorite Female Voice from an Animated Movie\n| [[Zendaya]]\n| {{nom}}\n|\n|-\n| [[Yara Shahidi]]\n| {{nom}}\n|\n|-\n| [[Visual Effects Society|Visual Effects Society Awards]]\n|[[17th Visual Effects Society Awards|February 5, 2019]]\n|Outstanding Effects Simulations in an Animated Feature\n| Henrik Karlsson, Theo Vandernoot, Martin Furness, Dmitriy Kolesnik\n|{{nom}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/artisans/awards/visual-effects-society-nominations-avengers-infinity-war-1203108109/|title=Avengers,\u2019 \u2018Lost in Space,\u2019 \u2018Ready Player One\u2019 Lead Visual Effects Society Nominations|work=Variety|first=Kristopher|last=Tapley|date=January 15, 2019|accessdate=January 17, 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== Possible sequel ==\nWriters [[Glenn Ficarra]] and [[John Requa]] have expressed hope for a sequel, with Requa stating that they \"could make a whole other movie just on that shtick that we came up with\". Ficarra added \"Hopefully, we are lucky enough to be in that position. But you have to wait for the world to digest it to a certain extent... We have a myriad of ideas. Just in the discarded notions that we have entertained over the last 6 years.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Wakeman|first=Gregory|title=Will there be a 'Smallfoot 2'? Here's what Channing Tatum, Common and its writers told us|url=https://www.metro.us/entertainment/movies/will-there-be-a-smallfoot-2|website=[[Metro New York]]|accessdate=November 3, 2018|date=September 28, 2018}}</ref> \n\n*''[[Smallfoot (film)|Smallfoot 2]]'' (2024)\n\n== See also ==\n*''[[The Son of Bigfoot]]''\n*''[[Missing Link (2019 film)|Missing Link]]\n*''[[Abominable (2019 film)|Abominable]]''\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{wikiquote}}\n*{{Official|http://www.smallfootmovie.com/}}\n*{{IMDb title|6182908}}\n\n{{Karey Kirkpatrick}}\n{{Warner Animation Group}}\n{{Warner Bros. animation and comics}}\n{{Warner Bros. theatrical animated features}}\n{{Portal bar|Cartoon|Animation|Comedy|Film|United States}}\n\n[[Category:2010s American animated films]]\n[[Category:2010s children's animated films]]\n[[Category:American adventure comedy films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American musical films]]\n[[Category:American musical comedy films]]\n[[Category:2018 films]]\n[[Category:2018 3D films]]\n[[Category:2018 computer-animated films]]\n[[Category:Warner Bros. Animation animated films]]\n[[Category:Warner Bros. films]]\n[[Category:Warner Bros. animated films]]\n[[Category:Films featuring anthropomorphic characters]]\n[[Category:Animated films based on children's books]]\n[[Category:Animated musical films]]\n[[Category:2010s musical films]]\n[[Category:2010s musical comedy films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Karey Kirkpatrick]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Heitor Pereira]]\n[[Category:Films set in Asia]]\n[[Category:Films set in the Himalayas]]\n[[Category:Films set in Nepal]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Karey Kirkpatrick]]\n[[Category:Yeti in fiction]]\n[[Category:Films about parallel universes]]\n[[Category:3D animated films]]\n[[Category:2010s children's adventure films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2018 film directed by Karey Kirkpatrick}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Smallfoot\n| image          = Smallfoot (film).png\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Karey Kirkpatrick]]\n| producer       = {{unbulleted list|Bonne Radford|[[Glenn Ficarra]]|[[John Requa]]}}\n| screenplay     = {{unbulleted list|Karey Kirkpatrick|Clare Sera}}\n| story          = {{unbulleted list|John Requa|Glenn Ficarra|Karey Kirkpatrick}}\n| based on       = {{based on|''Yeti Tracks'' (unpublished)|[[Sergio Pablos]]}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|<!--Per poster billing-->\n* [[Channing Tatum]]\n* [[James Corden]]\n* [[Zendaya]]\n* [[Common (rapper)|Common]]\n* [[LeBron James]]\n* [[Danny DeVito]]\n* [[Gina Rodriguez]]\n* [[Yara Shahidi]]\n* [[Ely Henry]]\n* [[Jimmy Tatro]]\n}}\n| music          = [[Heitor Pereira]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://filmmusicreporter.com/2017/11/21/heitor-pereira-to-score-smallfoot/|title=Heitor Pereira to Score 'Smallfoot'|website=Film Music Reporter|date=November 21, 2018|accessdate=November 25, 2018}}</ref>\n| cinematography          = Stephen W. Childers \n| editing        = Peter Ettinger\n| production companies = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Warner Animation Group]]\n* Zaftig Films<ref name=\"varietyinsight\">{{cite web |title=Film releases |url=https://www.varietyinsight.com/print_featurefilm_releases.php?sort=&from_date= |website=[[Variety Insight]] |publisher=[[Variety Media]] |accessdate=August 7, 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n| distributor    = [[Warner Bros.|Warner Bros. Pictures]]<ref name=\"varietyinsight\" />\n| released       = {{Film date|2018|9|28|United States}}\n| runtime        = 96 minutes<ref>{{cite web |title=Smallfoot (3D)|url=https://www.bbfc.co.uk/releases/smallfoot-film |website=[[British Board of Film Classification]]|date=September 14, 2018|accessdate=September 25, 2018}}</ref>\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         = $80 million<ref name=BOpreview/>\n| gross          = $214 million<ref name=\"BOM\">{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=smallfoot.htm|title=Smallfoot (2018)|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=January 7, 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Smallfoot''''' is a 2018 American  [[computer-animated]] [[Musical film|musical]] [[comedy film]] produced by the [[Warner Animation Group]] and distributed by [[Warner Bros.|Warner Bros. Pictures]]. Based on the unpublished children's book ''Yeti Tracks'' by [[Sergio Pablos]], the film was co-written and directed by [[Karey Kirkpatrick]], and stars the voices of [[Channing Tatum]], [[James Corden]], [[Zendaya]], [[Common (rapper)|Common]], [[LeBron James]], [[Gina Rodriguez]], [[Danny DeVito]], [[Yara Shahidi]], [[Ely Henry]], and [[Jimmy Tatro]]. The plot follows a group of [[Yeti]] who come across a human, with each species thinking the other was just a myth.\n\n''Smallfoot'' was theatrically released in the United States on September 28, 2018. It received a moderately positive reception from critics and was a box office success, grossing over $214 million worldwide.\n\n== Plot ==\n<!-- Per WP:FILMPLOT, plot summaries for featured film articles should be 400 to 700 words. -->\nA village of [[Yeti]]s lives in isolation on the top of a mountain in the [[Himalayas]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Mitchell|first=Peter|url=https://www.news.com.au/world/breaking-news/channing-tatum-belts-out-tune-in-smallfoot/news-story/8aad30b072ffad2b0e520d16a2fee43d|title=Channing Tatum belts out tune in Smallfoot|website=News.co.au|archivedate=September 20, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> above the clouds and hidden away from sight. Migo is a yeti who abides by the law of the ancient stones held by the Stonekeeper, the yetis' leader. Migo's father, Dorgle, projects himself through the air each morning to hit a gong with his head, as the yetis believe this allows the sun to rise. While learning how to ring the gong, Migo is distracted by the Stonekeeper's daughter, Meechee, whom he has a crush on, and misses the gong, landing outside the village. There, Migo witnesses a plane crash and finds a \"smallfoot\" (human), whom the yetis believe is mythical. Migo runs back to inform the villagers, but because he lacks proof, Stonekeeper claims he is lying and banishes him from the village. Migo is suddenly visited by rejected yetis Gwangi, Kolka, and Fleem who bring him to the Smallfoot Evidentiary Society, which is led by Meechee. She convinces Migo travel below the clouds despite the stones telling them that there is nothing underneath. After some hesitation, Migo agrees to go, but his rope snaps and Migo falls, where he discovers land.\n\nPercy Patterson is a British human filmmaker of wildlife documentaries who has lost most of his viewership. He meets the pilot who saw Migo, and in an attempt to regain his fame, tries unsuccessfully to convince his assistant, Brenda, to dress up as a yeti for filming. Migo arrives and unknowingly scares Percy when trying to communicate with him. Migo takes Percy with him and they stop in a cave to wait out a blizzard. Percy films and uploads a video of Migo narrating that the Yeti plans to eat him, before attempting to escape. While chasing Percy, Migo's toe becomes caught in a bear trap and Percy takes pity on him by removing the trap and bandaging Migo's wound. Percy agrees to go with Migo and they head back up the mountain, where they reunite with the S.E.S.\n\nThe villagers are confused by Percy's appearance, but happily accept him and learn about his culture, much to Stonekeeper's dismay. Afterwards, Stonekeeper takes Migo inside the palace and reveals the truth: yetis used to live below the clouds, but were forced into hiding by the humans who attacked them. To keep them safe, they created the stones, and the clouds are actually steam made by the yetis' daily tasks to keep them hidden. In order to protect the village, Migo agrees to continue the lie by telling the yetis that Percy, who is experiencing [[high altitude sickness]], is just a hairless [[wild yak]]. Stonekeeper takes Percy and locks him in a box, so Percy will be unable to alert other humans of the yetis' whereabouts. Migo later discovers that Meechee took Percy away to return him home, and jumps down the mountain with Gwangi and Kolka following suit.\n\nPercy recovers and discovers that his video of Migo has generated public excitement, but then notices that Meechee has become distracted by the wonders in [[Kathmandu]] and accidentally causes a disruption. Meechee is attacked by the police, but is rescued by Gwangi, Kolka and Migo. The yetis try to make it back to the mountain, but are chased by a SWAT helicopter that Stonekeeper takes down using his stones. Migo attempts to divert the police away from the other yetis, when Percy arrives on his snowmobile and shoots Migo with a tranquilizer gun to save him. The police chase and capture Percy in his yeti suit, and arrest him for public disturbance and fraud.\n\nBack at the village, inside the palace, Migo and Stonekeeper explain the truth to the yetis while Migo apologizes for lying to them. Migo tells the others that even though humans may still be scared of the yetis, they should try to communicate with them. The yetis leave the village, and when Percy and Brenda notice them, they emerge from the crowd and stand up for the yetis. The rest of the humans slowly welcome the yetis and accept them into their lives.\n\n== Voice cast ==\n*[[Channing Tatum]] as Migo, a young male [[yeti]] who is determined to prove the existence of the Smallfoot.\n*[[James Corden]] as Percy Patterson, a British [[human]] [[filmmaker]] of wildlife documentaries trying to get back in the spotlight, who becomes Migo's Smallfoot-best friend.\n*[[Zendaya]] as Meechee, a young female yeti, the Stonekeeper's daughter, Thorp's younger sister, the leader of S.E.S., and Migo's love interest.\n*[[Common (rapper)|Common]] as Stonekeeper, the condescending yeti [[Tribal chief|chief]] and father of Thorp and Meechee.\n*[[LeBron James]] as Gwangi, a large purple male yeti who is part of the S.E.S.\n*[[Gina Rodriguez]] as Kolka, a female yeti who is part of the S.E.S.\n*[[Danny DeVito]] as Dorgle, a short male yeti who is the village gong ringer and Migo's widowed father.\n*[[Yara Shahidi]] as Brenda, Percy's co-worker for his show and his morally conscious assistant, who doesn't believe in yetis until the end of the movie.\n*[[Ely Henry]] as Fleem, a small male yeti who is part of the S.E.S.\n*[[Jimmy Tatro]] as Thorp, a slow-witted male yeti who's the Stonekeeper's son and Meechee's older brother.\n*[[Patricia Heaton]] as Mama Bear, a [[himalayan brown bear]] that Migo and Percy encounter in a cave while waiting out a blizzard.  In the UK release, the part of Mama Bear was performed by [[Emma Bunton]]. \n*[[Justin Roiland]] as Garry, a paranoid male yeti.\n*[[Jack Quaid]] as Pilot, a human airplane pilot who crashes on the mountain and who Migo first meets.\n\n== Production ==\n[[File:Yeti by Philippe Semeria.jpg|thumb|The legend of the [[Yeti]] and an original idea by [[Sergio Pablos]] inspired the story.]]\nWriters [[Glenn Ficarra]] and [[John Requa]] conceived of ''Smallfoot'', interested in a story about [[Yeti]] or [[Bigfoot]]; they drew inspiration from an original idea by [[Sergio Pablos]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metro.us/entertainment/movies/is-smallfoot-based-on-a-book |title=Is 'Smallfoot' based on a book? |website=[[Metro New York]] |last=Wakeman |first=Gregory |date=September 28, 2018 |accessdate=October 8, 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe concept for ''Smallfoot'' was in development before director [[Karey Kirkpatrick]] joined the project in July 2016; he viewed an [[animatic]] in which Percy was a \"ski bum type\". Kirkpatrick also said Meechee was undeveloped, and she was made head of the S.E.S. in rewrites.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/smallfoot-director-karey-kirkpatrick-interview/|title=Director Karey Kirkpatrick Reveals How Current Events Shaped 'Smallfoot' |work=[[Collider.com]] |last=Cook |first=Tommy |date=October 5, 2018 |accessdate=October 8, 2018}}</ref> Observing [[Brexit]] and a rise in nationalism, Kirkpatrick also drew inspiration:\n{{quote|Truth was under attack ... certainly phrases like [[alternative facts]] were being thrown around.  So, it became an age of misinformation fueled by agendas that are often fueled by fear. And like, 'I want this result, and so I am skewing the truth.' That is just in the zeitgeist.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://screenrant.com/smallfoot-director-interview-karey-kirkpatrick/ |title=Karey Kirkpatrick Interview: Smallfoot|work=[[Screen Rant]] |last=Deckelmeier |first=Joe |date=September 28, 2018 |accessdate=October 8, 2018}}</ref>}}\n\nOn May 11, 2017, it was announced that the film was in-production with [[Channing Tatum]], [[Zendaya]], and [[Gina Rodriguez]] providing the lead voice roles.<ref name=\"May2017THR\">{{cite news|last1=Kit|first1=Borys|title=Channing Tatum, Zendaya, Gina Rodriguez Lead Voice Cast for Yeti Tale 'Smallfoot'|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/channing-tatum-zendaya-gina-rodriguez-lead-voice-cast-yeti-tale-smallfoot-1002860|accessdate=May 12, 2017|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=May 11, 2017|language=en}}</ref> [[Ely Henry]] was originally hired as a [[scratch vocal]] for the film four years before its release, however was later invited to join the cast and subsequently voiced Fleem in the final product.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://terroirmag.com/articles/2018/9/29/self-care-in-the-creative-industries-with-ely-henry |title=Self Care in the Creative Industries with Ely Henry \u2014 Terroir Magazine |publisher=Terroirmag.com |date=2018-09-29 |accessdate=2019-09-30}}</ref> The film was animated by [[Sony Pictures Imageworks]], who had also provided animation for the [[Warner Animation Group]]'s ''[[Storks (film)|Storks]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.awn.com/animationworld/warner-and-imageworks-deliver-more-babies-storks|title=Warner and Imageworks Deliver More than Babies in 'Storks'|first=Dan|last=Sarto|website=[[Animation World Network]]|date=September 22, 2016|accessdate=November 24, 2018}}</ref> and utilized [[Autodesk Maya]] for the animation process.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://postperspective.com/creating-snow-hair-environments-warners-smallfoot/|title=Sony Imageworks provides big effects, animation for Warner's Smallfoot|date=October 3, 2018|first=Randi|last=Altman|website=postperspective.com|accessdate=November 24, 2018}}</ref> Ryan O'Loughlin, a [[DreamWorks Animation]] veteran, was originally the film's director, but was replaced by Kirkpatrick.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cartoonbrew.com/feature-film/warner-bros-unveils-smallfoot-teaser-trailer-154933.html|title=Warner Bros. Unveils 'Smallfoot' Teaser Trailer|work=Cartoon Brew|date=November 22, 2017|last1=Amidi|first1=Amid|accessdate=November 28, 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Music ===\nThe score for the film was composed by [[Heitor Pereira]]. The songs were written by Karey and [[Wayne Kirkpatrick]]. The film originally had no songs until six months into production when the suggestion of making the film a musical came from [[Toby Emmerich]], who was recently elected as chairman of the Warner Bros. Pictures Group at the time.<ref>{{cite web|last=McLean|first=Tom|url=http://www.animationmagazine.net/features/smallfoot-singing-with-sasquatch-friends/|title='Smallfoot': Singing with Sasquatch & Friends|website=Animation Magazine|date=September 3, 2018|accessdate=November 25, 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe songs include \"Perfection\" by Channing Tatum, \"Wonderful Life\" by Zendaya, \"Percy's Pressure\" by James Corden (music from the song \"[[Under Pressure]]\", additional lyrics by Karey and Wayne Kirkpatrick), \"Wonderful Questions\" by Tatum & Zendaya, \"Let It Lie\" by [[Common (rapper)|Common]], \"Moment of Truth\" by CYN, and \"Finally Free\" by [[Niall Horan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://watertower-music.com/releases/release.php?title=smallfoot|title=Smallfoot: Original Motion Picture Soundtrack|website=WaterTower Music|access-date=October 3, 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\nThe film was released on September 28, 2018.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/festivals/annecy-warner-animation-group-smallfoot-1201795420/|title=Annecy: Warner Animation Group Sets 'Smallfoot' For a Spring 2018 Release|last=Hopewell|first=John|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=June 14, 2016|accessdate=May 12, 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Marketing ===\nThe first teaser trailer was released on November 22, 2017. The first official trailer was released on April 24, 2018. The final trailer was released on July 27, 2018. <ref>{{cite web |last1=Billington |first1=Alex |title=New Full-Length Trailer for Animated 'Smallfoot' Movie About Yetis |url=https://www.firstshowing.net/2018/official-full-length-trailer-for-animated-smallfoot-movie-about-yetis/|website=FirstShowing.net |date=April 25, 2018|accessdate=August 15, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn late summer 2018, American pizza chain [[Chuck E. Cheese's]] announced that they will be the official partner of the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ispot.tv/ad/dzFY/chuck-e-cheeses-all-you-can-play-smallfoot-collectible|title=Chuck E. Cheese's All You Can Play TV Commercial, 'Smallfoot Collectible'|website=iSpot.tv|language=en|accessdate=October 7, 2018}}</ref> Marketing materials for the film, in particular a series of posters in [[Los Angeles]] advertising the cast of the film with phrases such as \"[[Zendaya]] is Meechee\", turned into a minor [[Internet meme]] (in a short song by Gabriel Gundacker).<ref>{{cite news |last1=Bromwich |first1=Jonah |title=Zendaya Is Meechee Is a Post-Vine Vine |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/09/25/style/zendaya-is-meechee.html |accessdate=November 25, 2018 |work=The New York Times |date=September 25, 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Home media ===\n''Smallfoot'' was released on Digital on iTunes, Movies Anywhere, Microsoft Store, Vudu, and Amazon Prime on December 4, 2018, and on DVD, Blu-ray, Blu-Ray 3D,, and Digital Copy on December 11, 2018.<ref>https://www.mediaplaynews.com/smallfoot-to-march-to-digital-dec-4-disc-dec-11-from-warner/</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.target.com/p/smallfoot-blu-ray-dvd-digital/-/A-54150093|title=Smallfoot (Blu-Ray + DVD + Digital)|website=Target|accessdate=November 24, 2018}}</ref> The releases also included a short film, titled ''Super Soozie''.\n\n== Reception ==\n=== Box office ===\n''Smallfoot'' grossed $83.2 million in the United States and Canada, and $130.9 million in other territories, for a total worldwide gross of $214.1 million.<ref name=\"BOM\"/>\n\nIn the United States and Canada, ''Smallfoot'' was released alongside ''[[Night School (2018 film)|Night School]]'', ''[[Little Women (2018 film)|Little Women]]'' and ''[[Hell Fest]]'', and was projected to gross $25\u201330 million from 4,131 theaters in its opening weekend.<ref name=BOpreview>{{cite web |url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/la-fi-ct-movie-projector-small-foot-night-school-20180926-story.html|title=Kevin Hart and Tiffany Haddish's 'Night School' to battle 'Smallfoot' for box office crown|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|first=Ryan|last=Faughnder|date=September 26, 2018|accessdate=September 26, 2018}}</ref> The film made $6.5 million on its first day, including $850,000  from Thursday night previews, more than the Warner Animation Group's previous September release ''[[Storks (film)|Storks]]'' ($435,000 in 2016). It went on to debut to $23 million, finishing second at the box office behind ''Night School''.<ref name=opening>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/09/night-school-tiffany-haddish-kevin-hart-weekend-box-office-1202472883/|title='Night School' Top Of The Weekend's Box Office Class With $28M; Best Opening For A Comedy So Far This Year|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |publisher=[[Penske Business Media]] |date=September 30, 2018 |first=Anthony |last=D'Alessandro |accessdate=September 30, 2018}}</ref> It made $14.3 million in its second weekend and $9.1 million in its third, dropping 37% each time and finishing third and fifth, respectively.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/venom-a-star-is-born-weekend-box-office-lady-gaga-1202476614/|title='Venom' Flies To Near $90M; 'A Star Is Born' Has Rhythm With $51M As Monday Fall Holidays Propel Box Office|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|publisher=[[Penske Business Media]]|date=October 9, 2018 |first=Anthony |last= D'Alessandro|accessdate=October 9, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/first-man-landing-1m-from-thursday-night-shows-early-b-o-read-1202481481/|title='Sony Swings Past $1 Billion As 'Venom' Bites $35M+; 'First Man' Lands Third With $16M+ \u2013 Sunday AM|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|publisher=[[Penske Business Media]]|date=October 14, 2018 |first=Anthony |last= D'Alessandro|accessdate=October 14, 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Critical response ===\nOn [[review aggregator]] [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film holds an approval rating of 76% based on 122 reviews, with an [[Weighted arithmetic mean|average rating]] of 6.26/10. The website's critical consensus reads, \"''Smallfoot'' offers a colorful distraction that should keep younger viewers entertained - and a story whose message might even resonate with older audiences.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/smallfoot|title=Smallfoot (2018)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=February 7, 2020}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], the film has a weighted average score of 60 out of 100, based on 25 critics, indicating \"mixed or average reviews\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/smallfoot|title=Smallfoot reviews|website=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=October 15, 2018}}</ref> Audiences polled by [[CinemaScore]] gave the film an average grade of \"A\u2013\" on an A+ to F scale, while [[PostTrak]] reported filmgoers gave it 4 out of 5 stars.<ref name=opening/>\n\n=== Accolades ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Award/Event\n! Date of ceremony\n! Category\n! Recipient(s) and nominee(s)\n! Result\n! class=\"unsortable\"| {{Abbr|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Alliance of Women Film Journalists]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"|January 10, 2019\n| Best Animated Feature Film\n| [[Karey Kirkpatrick]]<br />Jason Reisig\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news |title=2018 EDA Award Nominees - Alliance of Women Film Journalists |url=https://awfj.org/eda-awards-2/2018-eda-award-nominees/ |accessdate=December 21, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best Animated Female\n| [[Zendaya]] <small>as Meechee</small>\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Annie Award]]s\n| February 2, 2019\n| [[Annie Award for Music in a Feature Production]] \n| Heitor Pereira, [[Karey Kirkpatrick]], [[Wayne Kirkpatrick]] \n| {{Nominated}} \n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|last=Flores|first=Terry|title=\u2018Incredibles 2,\u2019 \u2018Ralph Breaks the Internet\u2019 Top Annie Awards Nominations|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/incredibles-2-ralph-annie-awards-nominations-1203077216/|publisher=Variety|accessdate=December 7, 2018|date=December 3, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Detroit Film Critics Society]]\n| December 3, 2018\n| Best Animated Feature\n| rowspan=\"2\"|''Smallfoot''\n| {{nom}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news |title=The 2018 Detroit Film Critics Society Awards |url=https://detroitfilmcritics.com/the-2018-detroit-film-critics-society-awards/ |accessdate=December 21, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Heartland Film Festival]]\n| October 11\u201321, 2018\n| Truly Moving Picture Award\n| {{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news |title=Truly Moving Picture Award - Heartland Film |url=http://heartlandfilm.org/tmpa/ |accessdate=December 21, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Hollywood Music in Media Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[9th Hollywood Music in Media Awards|November 14, 2018]]\n| Original Score \u2013 Animated Film\n| [[Heitor Pereira]] \n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"HMMA18\">{{cite news |last1=Xu |first1=Linda |title=Hollywood 